-- Nordex Wins 80-Megawatt Turbine Order From Iberdrola in Romania
-- B y   S t e f a n   N i c o l a
-- 2012-12-11T13:21:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-11/nordex-wins-80-megawatt-turbine-order-from-iberdrola-in-romania.html
Nordex SE (NDX1) , a German maker of  wind
turbines , won an order from  Iberdrola SA (IBE)  to supply a 80-megawatt
farm in  Romania .  Nordex will supply 32 of its 2.5-megawatt machines to the
Chirnogeni wind farm near the Black Sea coast built by
Iberdrola, the Hamburg-based company said today in a statement.
The turbines are expected to start operating in late 2013, it
said.  The project will be owned and operated by a group comprised
of Marguerite Fund, EnerCap Power Fund and EP Global Energy Ltd,
Nordex said. The European Bank for Reconstruction and
Development and a group of commercial banks including Erste
Bank, ING and UniCredit provided financing, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
